                     Oh, Hill.  

02:10.797 --> 02:12.865
                What, are you on
                  an ugly break?

02:12.932 --> 02:15.034
Oh, my.                         
Someone certainly got up        

02:15.101 --> 02:17.970
on the wrong side of town       
this morning.                   

02:20.707 --> 02:23.842
        What's the matter, Hill,
        your scalp on too tight?

02:27.414 --> 02:29.381
                Very funny.     

02:29.449 --> 02:31.483
              Free this evening?

02:31.551 --> 02:34.153
Just get it                     
through your hairy ears,        

02:34.220 --> 02:35.521
whatever happened               
between us                      

02:35.588 --> 02:37.690
was strictly                    
a seven-night stand.            

02:37.757 --> 02:39.625
                    Oh...       

02:39.693 --> 02:41.560
You're forgetting...            

02:41.628 --> 02:45.764
    All right, seven nights, two
lunch breaks, and a bus ride.   

02:45.832 --> 02:49.735
I love slumming with you.       

02:49.803 --> 02:51.337
                      Well, just
                      forget it.

02:51.404 --> 02:53.872
    Today is Elvis' birthday,   
         and I'm not interested.

02:53.940 --> 02:55.574
                Get out of here.

02:55.642 --> 02:57.710
    Okay, but if you change     
        your mind,              

02:57.777 --> 03:00.112
 you know where you can get me. 

03:00.180 --> 03:02.981
        Good Lord,              
  do you know where to get me.  

03:04.684 --> 03:06.352
             Woof!              

03:08.521 --> 03:10.789
      I can't believe it.       

03:10.857 --> 03:12.491
What is it, Sam?                

03:12.559 --> 03:13.692
    (clearing throat):          
             Oh...              

03:13.760 --> 03:15.794
          Tony, my hairstylist--

03:15.862 --> 03:19.264
  he's making a left on Boylston
    and this bus cut him off.   

03:19.332 --> 03:20.399
            Car jumped the curb,

03:20.467 --> 03:22.034
             and he slammed into
              this hot dog stand

03:22.102 --> 03:23.535
             and ended up in the
              middle of the pond

03:23.603 --> 03:25.070
                in the public   
                        gardens.

03:25.138 --> 03:27.573
        He's at the hospital now
        with two broken legs.   

03:27.640 --> 03:30.109
                Got to cancel my
            hair appointment.   

03:33.146 --> 03:36.448
            I hate it when stuff
        like that happens to me.

03:36.516 --> 03:38.017
(door opens)                    

03:38.184 --> 03:39.651
        Greetings, all.         

03:39.753 --> 03:41.253
I have a brief                  
announcement.                   

03:41.321 --> 03:42.988
    You may recall last year    

03:43.056 --> 03:45.224
          I brought in          
 my dysfunctional men's group.  

03:45.291 --> 03:46.325
Well, unfortunately,            

03:46.393 --> 03:47.760
my low self-esteem group        
heard about it                  

03:47.827 --> 03:49.395
and now they think              
they're not good enough.        

03:51.564 --> 03:53.365
 So you're bringing them here?  

03:53.466 --> 03:55.601
    Well, I'd like the group    
    to get used to a normal,    

03:55.669 --> 03:57.336
  healthy, social environment.  

03:57.404 --> 03:59.605
 So you're bringing them here?  

03:59.673 --> 04:01.040
  Look, all I'm asking, guys,   

04:01.107 --> 04:04.176
     is that you treat them     
    as if they were at home.    

04:04.244 --> 04:07.246
You know, they've all been      
wounded and they're vulnerable, 

04:07.313 --> 04:09.248
        and, well, the truth is,

04:09.315 --> 04:12.017
    you'll never find           
a sadder group of people.       

04:12.085 --> 04:13.352
Oh, yeah?                       

04:13.453 --> 04:15.087
How about                       
the Donner party?               

04:15.155 --> 04:17.755
Well, you know, they-they       
got lost in the mountains       

04:17.824 --> 04:19.858
and had to watch                
their limbs freeze off          

04:19.926 --> 04:21.293
while they ate each other.      

04:22.395 --> 04:24.430
    Well, you caught me.        

04:24.497 --> 04:27.766
    Cannibalism <i>is</i> sadder       
    than low self-esteem.       

04:29.469 --> 04:31.503
                Carla, what's   
                    the date?   

04:31.571 --> 04:32.905
Don't you know?                 

04:33.006 --> 04:34.873
(chuckling):                    
Rebecca, on this date           

04:34.974 --> 04:39.144
            in 1935,            
 Elvis Aaron Presley was born.  

04:39.212 --> 04:41.013
A man who was destined          

04:41.081 --> 04:43.215
      to change the shape       
    of popular music.           

04:43.283 --> 04:45.751
    A man who captured          
     the hearts of America.     

04:45.819 --> 04:47.486
        A man who,              
      through his music...      

04:47.554 --> 04:48.954
Can I have my drink?            

04:52.225 --> 04:55.661
...taught us all                
the meaning of love.            

04:56.930 --> 04:58.997
         Listen, I have         
a question for you, Tony.       

04:59.065 --> 05:01.633
    Uh, are your arms broken    
            as well,            

05:01.701 --> 05:04.603
or is it j-just the legs?       

05:04.671 --> 05:06.338
  Just the legs are shattered.  

05:06.406 --> 05:08.707
        (quietly):              
        All right!              

05:08.775 --> 05:10.109
Say, all right, Tony,           

05:10.210 --> 05:12.411
maybe if I showed up there      
    with some scissors          

05:12.479 --> 05:15.180
I could lean over the bed       
         and y... Tony?         

05:15.248 --> 05:17.783
Tony, don't-don't pass out      
          on me, man.           

05:17.851 --> 05:18.884
        Hello?                  

05:18.952 --> 05:20.552
        Who's this?             

05:20.620 --> 05:22.021
      You're his nurse?         

05:22.088 --> 05:23.188
  Ah, great.                    

05:23.256 --> 05:26.792
Listen, honey, do you           
cut hair by any chance?         

05:26.860 --> 05:28.594
  Hello? Shoot!                 

05:29.629 --> 05:31.864
     I hate this.               

05:31.931 --> 05:36.201
I can hear the little hairs     
scraping along my collar.       

05:36.269 --> 05:39.505
Can you hear that,              
or is that just me?             

05:40.907 --> 05:43.175
         Hey, Sam, why don't you
        let me cut your hair?   

05:43.243 --> 05:45.144
      (laughs)                  

05:45.245 --> 05:46.745
    (snorts)                    

05:46.813 --> 05:48.814
That's cute, man,               
that's very funny.              

05:48.882 --> 05:51.517
Took my mind off                
my hair there                   
for a minute.                   

05:53.219 --> 05:54.286
        No, Sam, I'm serious.   

05:54.354 --> 05:55.821
        I-I'm pretty good at it.

05:55.889 --> 05:57.790
            I cut Dr. Crane's   
                      hair once.

05:57.857 --> 06:00.726
Yes, uh, he did, and I must say 
    he did an excellent job.    

06:00.794 --> 06:02.795
No, I don't know,               
Woody, I don't know.            

06:02.862 --> 06:04.396
        Sam, look, all right,   

06:04.464 --> 06:07.399
      let me just trim the back,
just to get it off the collar   

06:07.467 --> 06:09.234
            so you don't have   
                to listen to it.

06:10.303 --> 06:12.438
                So <i>we</i> don't have
                to listen to it.

06:12.505 --> 06:14.340
SAM:                            
All right, just                 
the back, though.               

06:14.441 --> 06:16.041
This is what                    
we're gonna need:               

06:16.109 --> 06:18.444
sterile                         
tungsten steel scissors,        

06:18.511 --> 06:22.448
English bone comb,              
36 to 39 tines,                 

06:22.515 --> 06:24.817
and a conditioner               
with a pro-vitamin              

06:24.884 --> 06:26.919
B-5 keratin complex.            

06:26.986 --> 06:28.120
         Got that?              

06:28.188 --> 06:31.890
                 And this little
              tool of the trade.

06:38.298 --> 06:41.934
Take the bowl                   
off the head.                   

06:42.002 --> 06:45.304
                     (laughing):
                Sam, it's just a
            little barber humor.

06:45.372 --> 06:46.372
                    (chuckles)  

06:46.439 --> 06:47.940
                     Come on!   

06:48.008 --> 06:49.074
        No, it's, like, uh...   

06:49.142 --> 06:51.477
              All right, what do
              you say to someone

06:51.544 --> 06:53.379
              who just had their
                ears lowered?   

06:53.446 --> 06:55.247
Oh, darn, I blew the joke.      

06:55.315 --> 06:57.249
All right...                    

