07:28.548 --> 07:30.883
    Oh, that's right,           
      that's his ride. Oh.      

07:30.950 --> 07:33.786
      Well, all right, uh,      
  the rest of you, uh, mingle.  

07:33.853 --> 07:35.187
            (chuckles)          

07:35.255 --> 07:38.657
                No, no. Boys,   
                what we're doing
            here is huddling.   

07:38.725 --> 07:41.493
You do know the difference      
 between huddling and mingling? 

07:41.561 --> 07:42.995
                     (mumbling):
        I know how to mingle.   

07:43.063 --> 07:44.563
     I just don't want to mingle
    with people I don't know.   

07:44.631 --> 07:46.331
Yes, that's right, Lester.      
        (chuckles)              

07:46.399 --> 07:47.833
            Frasier, I didn't   
            quite catch that.   

07:47.901 --> 07:49.401
 Truth be told, neither did I.  

07:49.469 --> 07:52.137
  I haven't understood a thing  
 the poor sap's said in years.  

07:52.205 --> 07:53.806
                         LILITH:
                        Frasier,

07:53.873 --> 07:56.942
I must restate my objection     
to your bringing them here.     

07:57.010 --> 07:59.244
As I've said previously,        
this is an extremely risky      

07:59.312 --> 08:01.280
and somewhat                    
frivolous experiment,           

08:01.381 --> 08:03.182
which could have                
negative repercussions.         

08:03.249 --> 08:06.018
            Oh, Wilma, loosen up
              the bone a little!

08:06.086 --> 08:08.420
This is an uncontrolled         
environment                     

08:08.488 --> 08:10.622
which could easily              
get out of hand.                

08:10.690 --> 08:12.624
And who's this Wilma?           

08:14.494 --> 08:16.895
        Are you sure you know   
              what you're doing?

08:16.963 --> 08:18.397
I think so.                     

08:20.266 --> 08:23.035
        Oh, is that some        
     of your barber humor?      

08:23.103 --> 08:25.070
Come on, lighten up, Sam!       

08:35.315 --> 08:38.583
Say, where's your               
sense of humor, man?            

08:38.650 --> 08:40.519
      Whoo!                     

08:40.587 --> 08:41.787
Airplane ride?                  

08:41.855 --> 08:43.455
Whoo!                           

08:43.523 --> 08:44.957
         Don't, don't do that.  

08:45.025 --> 08:46.959
Round trip? Whoo!               

08:50.530 --> 08:51.563
                         So...  

08:51.631 --> 08:53.032
you from around here?           

08:53.099 --> 08:54.600
            Woody...            

08:54.668 --> 08:56.835
         just get to it,        
        will you, please?       

08:56.903 --> 08:58.637
Hey, suit yourself.             
    Same price.                 

08:58.705 --> 09:00.539
        (shaver buzzing)        

09:03.476 --> 09:05.277
It's all right, Sam. Okay.      

09:13.753 --> 09:18.023
    So, uh, you're the guys     
with low self-esteem, huh?      

09:19.459 --> 09:23.429
Yeah, well, luckily,            
I don't have that problem.      

09:23.496 --> 09:25.397
  But then again, how could I?  

09:25.465 --> 09:27.066
  What, with a cerebral cortex  

09:27.133 --> 09:29.968
  that's eight percent larger   
than the average human's.       

09:31.371 --> 09:33.605
          Don't look--          
        you can't tell.         

09:33.673 --> 09:37.676
    E-Excuse me, do you wear    
that mailman uniform every day? 

09:37.744 --> 09:38.744
        Yes, I do.              

09:38.812 --> 09:40.245
          And proudly.          

09:40.313 --> 09:41.780
 Do you live with your mother?  

09:43.950 --> 09:46.618
    Well, uh... yeah.           

09:46.686 --> 09:47.820
Yeah.                           

09:47.887 --> 09:50.356
     Hey, guys, it's Mr. X.     

09:53.360 --> 09:55.761
        Uh, gentlemen, let me   
         show you the pool room.

09:55.829 --> 09:57.730
                      (chuckles)
                        Quickly.

09:57.797 --> 09:59.398
      (quietly):                
  That's the guy...             

09:59.466 --> 10:00.866
                     Come along.

10:00.934 --> 10:03.268
              And that must be  
        Mr. X's fat friend,     

10:03.336 --> 10:05.371
             Mr. Y, at the end  
                of the bar!     

10:10.543 --> 10:12.845
        (shaver buzzing)        

10:12.912 --> 10:14.813
        (bubblegum pops)        

10:19.219 --> 10:21.353
    (shaver turns off)          

10:21.421 --> 10:23.522
          Oops.                 

10:23.590 --> 10:25.024
    What do you mean, "oops"?   

10:25.091 --> 10:26.692
     What's going on back there?

10:26.760 --> 10:28.127
    Oh, nothing, Sam.           

10:28.194 --> 10:30.396
Uh, say, when you came in,      

10:30.463 --> 10:33.499
    did you have...             
gum in your hair?               

10:34.834 --> 10:36.301
            No. Why?            

10:36.369 --> 10:37.770
    No reason.                  

10:37.837 --> 10:41.373
I'm just trying to pass         
    the time of day.            

10:41.441 --> 10:43.342
            Aw...               

10:43.410 --> 10:46.745
     Damn it, Woody, you got gum
    in my hair, didn't you?     

10:46.813 --> 10:48.981
Uh, no, no. Here, here.         

10:49.049 --> 10:51.116
        (shaver buzzing)        
        There.                  

10:51.184 --> 10:52.484
            Out.                

10:53.987 --> 10:55.554
            What's it look like?

10:55.622 --> 10:58.390
 It's got a lot of hair in it.  

10:58.458 --> 11:00.893
Give me that other mirror.      

11:02.295 --> 11:04.096
Give me the other mirror, Woody!

11:04.164 --> 11:05.664
                            SAM:
                          Woody!

11:24.417 --> 11:27.486
Want to go over and say hi,     
make 'em feel more at home?     

11:27.554 --> 11:30.356
             I don't know, those
             guys are wrapped up
                pretty tight.   

11:30.423 --> 11:32.324
      Who knows how loony       
        they could get?         

11:32.392 --> 11:33.759
    They might be dangerous.    

11:33.827 --> 11:35.260
    They might buy us a beer.   

11:35.328 --> 11:37.730
        I'll do anything        
to promote mental health.       

11:41.601 --> 11:44.503
So, uh, Wynken,                 
Blynken and Nod...              

11:44.571 --> 11:45.637
I know they're alive.           

11:45.705 --> 11:46.739
I can hear                      
them breathing.                 

11:46.806 --> 11:49.308
        Rebecca, give us        
      a pitcher, will you?      

11:49.376 --> 11:51.477
  (all chatting and laughing)   

11:55.515 --> 11:59.318
     So... uh, what are we      
      talking about here?       

11:59.386 --> 12:00.619
Oh, I'm sorry, Dr. Crane.       

12:00.687 --> 12:02.388
     We were kind of making     
        fun of somebody.        

12:02.455 --> 12:04.023
    Oh, no. No need             
    to be sorry.                

12:04.090 --> 12:05.424
     Listen, it's a             
perfectly healthy sign.         

12:05.492 --> 12:06.658
It, it means that               

12:06.726 --> 12:07.826
you're interacting,             

12:07.894 --> 12:09.294
that you're feeling             
better about yourselves.        

12:09.362 --> 12:12.297
So, uh, what were you           
saying about this poor sap?     

12:12.365 --> 12:13.632
        (laughter)              

12:13.700 --> 12:16.268
That he's a pompous fool.       

12:17.971 --> 12:19.705
  Oh, Cliff is just             
  trying to fit in.             

12:22.509 --> 12:24.443
              We weren't talking
                    about Cliff.

12:24.511 --> 12:26.345
                 We were talking
         about you... "egghead."

12:26.413 --> 12:28.180
        (laughter)              

12:29.582 --> 12:31.517
        Me?                     

12:31.584 --> 12:33.352
Hey, remember the time          
Fras fell asleep,               

12:33.420 --> 12:35.821
and we, we put his hand         
in that warm glass of water?    

12:37.290 --> 12:39.625
        That's the first time   
        I ever saw that work.   

12:40.960 --> 12:42.628
    Okay, we can                
    stop this now.              

12:42.696 --> 12:43.896
Hey, remember that time Carla   
        put the green,          

12:43.963 --> 12:46.732
        uh, marble              
     in his martini glass?      

12:46.800 --> 12:47.966
Carla did that?                 

12:48.034 --> 12:50.436
I broke a crown.                

12:50.503 --> 12:53.172
Well, how about the time he,    
he leaned over his mai tai      

12:53.239 --> 12:55.374
and, uh, poked his eye          
with the umbrella.              

12:55.442 --> 12:58.944
 Look, there is nothing amusing 
    about corneal abrasion.     

12:59.012 --> 13:03.082
        How about the time at   
    group when he leaned back   

13:03.149 --> 13:04.883
      in his chair to make      
    a dramatic gesture          

13:04.951 --> 13:05.918
      and he got stuck in       
      the venetian blinds.      

13:05.985 --> 13:07.119
NORM:                           
He did?!                        

13:07.187 --> 13:09.588
            Now that's funny.   

13:09.656 --> 13:10.989
    No it's not.                

13:11.057 --> 13:15.461
    Did you hear that? He       
    said, "No, it's snot."      

13:15.528 --> 13:17.129
        Oh, this is not         
        therapy.                

13:17.197 --> 13:19.198
    This is just                
    childish abuse.             

13:19.265 --> 13:21.133
      So we put an end          
      to it right here.         

13:21.201 --> 13:22.434
    This, this session          
    is over,                    

13:22.502 --> 13:24.970
 right now.                     

13:25.038 --> 13:28.707
      Remember, it's a fee      
         and a half...          

13:28.775 --> 13:31.377
because it's a field trip.      

13:34.714 --> 13:37.383
      Gee, maybe we should      
      go apologize to him.      

13:37.450 --> 13:38.550
He's charging you               
a fee and a half,               

13:38.618 --> 13:39.685
and you want to apologize?      

13:39.753 --> 13:41.053
    Well, what should we do?    

13:41.121 --> 13:42.554
        Pants him.              

13:42.622 --> 13:43.856
CLIFF:                          
There you go.                   
Yeah.                           

13:43.923 --> 13:45.991
     Yeah, let's pants him!     

13:46.059 --> 13:48.327
                Let's go for it!
Pants him.                      

13:48.395 --> 13:49.995
                     (chanting):
        Pants him. Pants him.   

